Author: wookie#7663
Content: I'm considering getting a z9 or z9mini for "hobby" mining. I've never used these miners before. I've watched a bunch of youtube videos and read some websites, one question I can't find an answer to is: is it possible to use a vpn to route the data?

Author: ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢#7004
Content: anything is possible, but why would you want to?

Author: ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢#7004
Content: you want *less* hops, not more

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: i don't think they care about VPNs, but latency matters

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: slow internet is worse for mining, fast internet is good

Author: wookie#7663
Content: the internet I go through has blocked me from mining before

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: oh, well then

Author: wookie#7663
Content: so I have a vpn on my gpus now

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: https://github.com/sshuttle/sshuttle

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: that piece of software is art, a full blown vpn in a single python app, can do tcp/udp/dns and more

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: i often use it to tunnel all my traffic thru a remote server

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: say you are getting blocked because of your country from a website .... perfect use case there 😃 And your use case, it tunnels all traffic over ssh, so screw the people filtering your internet

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: there are people here much more knowledgeable than me, but basically, the z9m is just a linux box. You can ssh into it

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: it gets a DHCP IP address by default

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: but as long as it has internet somehow, it doesn't care

Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: all it cares about is sending hashpower to a pool URL

Author: ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢#7004
Content:
`the z9m is just a linux box. You can ssh into it`
more specifically a nix box running cgminer (well a bastardized version of it anyway)

Content: thanks, will definiitely take a look!
